    "V1 random-access caveat: per-group k makes row r's escape-code bit offset an O(ng) weighted prefix (sum k_g*cnt_g) derivable from the stored count prefix + k side stream, not baseline stz's O(1) k*prefix[r]; a strictly-O(1) stored per-group code-offset table is NOT charged and would cost ~_pw(bits)*ng extra bits (~0.01 b/w at group=1 on a 5M-param tensor) -- same order as V1's expected gain, so read group=1 V1 gains with that caveat (or assume a load-time-derived offset table)"
